Sania Mirza-Barbora Strycova in Indian Wells quarters, Leander Paes crashes out 
12-3-2017 
Sania Mirza and her Czech partner Barbora Strycova scored a straight sets win to enter the women’s doubles quarter-finals of the BNP Paribas Open 2017 tennis tournament (Indian Wells) in Miami on Saturday.

The Indo-Czech pair needed around 64 minutes to beat Sara Errani of Italy and Alicja Rosolska of Poland 6-2, 6-3.

Sania and her partner were stronger with their serve, hitting three aces, while Errani and Rosolska committed three double faults.

Read more | Davis Cup: Rubbers to be best-of-three affairs, Rafael Nadal not amused

Sania Mirza and Strycova had entered the second round at Indian Wells after defeating German-Latvian duo of Julia Goerges and Jelena Ostapenko 6-3, 6-4.

But Indian fans faced disappointment in the men’s doubles as Leander Paes and his Argentine partner Juan Martin del Potro went down 3-6, 4-6 to American Sam Querrey and Gilles Müller of Luxembourg.

Read more | Andy Murray, world No.1, loses to Vasek Pospisil in Indian Wells tournament

Querrey and Muller smashed six aces against just two by Paes-Potro to chalk out a win in just over an hour. 
